image:image.image:title: Report Incident - Suspicious Activity
image:image.image:caption: Call 911 immediately if you notice suspicious activity! The sooner police know about a suspicious incident, the easier it is to find out whether there is a threat to people or property. Don’t question your instincts; we want to know!

image:image.image:title: Report Incident - Code Violations
image:image.image:caption: Email Code Enforcement Office for code violations at sblasko@rogersmn.gov or call 612-490-1796 during normal office hours.

image:image.image:title: Report Incident - Animal Issues
image:image.image:caption: If you have lost or found an animal, contact the Police Department at 763-428-3450 during business hours, or non-emergency dispatch at 952-258-5321 during non-business hours. If you have an animal complaint or concern call non-emergency dispatch at 952-258-5321.

image:image.image:title: Crime Prevention - Elderly Scams
image:image.image:caption: This guide covers the various fraud tactics that scammers commonly use, followed by more detail on each type of fraud. Last but not least, if you suspect that you or someone you know may be a victim of a scam, briefly review the resources you can turn to. View the article here.

image:image.image:title: Police Ordinances - Alarms
image:image.image:caption: Three or more false alarms within a calendar year is excessive, constitutes a public nuisance, and shall be unlawful. Civil penalties for false alarms for an alarm system may be assessed against an alarm user, as provided in the city's current fee schedule. Reference Ordinance Sec. 14-59 through 14-63 for more details.

image:image.image:title: Lock Box - Lock Box
image:image.image:caption: -Select your location: Minnesota -Type your local fire department/agency: Rogers Fire Dept -Click Search Three Options will appear for selection: 1. Commercial Knox Products 2. FDC Products only 3. Residential Use Only-Home Boxes The 3200 style commercial box is acceptable for most commercial applications. Locking FDC caps are required on all new commercial buildings and any existing buildings in which caps are missing. Residential boxes are not required, but are available to any resident who wishes to install one.

image:image.image:title: Streets - ADA Transition Plan
image:image.image:caption: The City of Rogers is committed to breaking down barriers for residents and to be a fair, inclusive and equitable community in its practices, programs and services. The American with Disabilities Act (ADA) enacted on July 26th, 1990, is a civil rights law prohibiting discrimination against individuals based on disability. The ADA requires public transportation agencies to develop transition plans detailing how the agencies will ensure accessibility within the public right of way. The City of Rogers Public Works Department has prepared this Americans with Disabilities Act ADA transition plan to guide its efforts to ensure pedestrian facilities located within the City’s right of way meet the accessibility needs of all residents.

image:image.image:title: Streets - Pavement Management
image:image.image:caption: The City of Rogers’ Pavement Management Program is designed to track the condition of City streets and to outline the costs associated with regular street maintenance projects including reconstructions, mill and overlay, concrete and storm sewer repairs, and utility relocation.

image:image.image:title: Community Gardens - Lions Central Park Garden
image:image.image:caption: The Lions Central Park Garden is located on the south side of Rogers in the South East corner of the former Triangle Park. This garden features 12 raised bed plots. All plots are 6 x 12 feet. There are six parking spots available, as well as street parking. Water access is on site.

image:image.image:title: Community Gardens - Water Tower Garden
image:image.image:caption: The Water Tower Garden is located on the north side of Rogers near Hassan Elementary. This garden features fourteen plots. All plots are 14 x 14 feet. There are six off street parking spots available. Water access is on site.

image:image.image:title: Play Ball! Minnesota Youth Clinic - 2019 Play Ball! Minnesota Youth Clinic
image:image.image:caption: Minnesota Twins Community Fund will be offering a FREE youth baseball/softball skills clinic in Rogers. Learn/review fundamentals including fielding, throwing and hitting. It is hands on instruction for boys and girls, so bring a baseball/softball glove and a water bottle. Other equipment is supplied by the foundation for the clinic. New in 2019, online registration/waiver signature for the clinic is available at www.playballmn.com. Forgot to register in advance, no problem, just show up as waiver forms will be available at the location on day and have FUN! Questions, call Cherie at 763-428-0975. When: Saturday, May 4th Time: Ages 6-9 10:00 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. Ages 10-13 11:30 a.m. – 1:00 p.m. Location: North Community Park (NCP) 13750 Bittersweet St, Rogers Back-up Location if Inclement Weather: Rogers Middle School 20855 – 141st Ave, Rogers Weather Hotline 763.428.0960

image:image.image:title: About Rogers Wines and Spirits
image:image.image:caption: Rogers Municipal Liquor Store features a generous selection of fine wines and spirits, with a friendly and knowledgeable staff to assist customers. The store is owned and managed by the City of Rogers; profits from the liquor store directly support public services and projects. The Roger's Liquor Department is dedicated to controlling the dispensation of alcohol in Rogers while simultaneously generating much needed revenue for the citizens it serves.
